{"key":"post-5340565","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>5340565</id>\n<content>Correct.  If you'll keep your master cultures in the refrigerator in test tubes, you can remove a very small piece once every few months to keep fresh material for growing.  Once a year, remove a small piece from the test tube, and let it grow in a petri dish for three days or so, then remove a small piece from the petri dish and use it to inoculate a fresh test tube.  If you'll do this, you can keep the same culture for twenty years or more without any problems from senesence.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>5340859</next>\n<prev>5340525</prev>\n<first>5339824</first>\n<last>5340859</last>\n<when>1140975453</when>\n<utime>02/26/06 07:37 PM</utime>\n</post>"}